Print sim_results object

Source: R/print.sim_results.R
print.sim_results.Rd

Print sim_results object

Usage

# S3 method for sim_results
print(x, ...)

Arguments

x

sim_results object; returned by the sim function

...

further arguments passed to or from other methods; none specified

Value

sim_results object is invisibly returned (the x param)

Examples


library(terra)

n1_small <- rast(system.file("input_maps/n1_small.tif", package = "rangr"))
K_small <- rast(system.file("input_maps/K_small.tif", package = "rangr"))

sim_data <- initialise(
  n1_map = n1_small,
  K_map = K_small,
  r = log(2),
  rate = 1 / 1e3
)
#> NaN values were found in input maps and replaced with NA (cells outside the study area)
sim_res <- sim(obj = sim_data, time = 20, burn = 5)
print(sim_res)
